race.comment: SHUTTER (2) caught the eye first-up, then followed it up with a barnstorming win at Scone. Has returned in terrific order and can keep the ball rolling. ALPINE ROSE (6) is ticking along superbly, finish in the top two in her last five starts. Loves the mile and is drawn kind. Obvious threat. SAINT PHILOMENA (7) doesn't win out of turn but is a track and trip winner, and gets the key booking of Nock from the inside draw. Have to take seriously. GHAZNAVI (5) has been a flashing light in his last two and can give them a late scare if they overdo it in front. ZELESTIAL (3) is knocking on the door and gets an important claim through Stiff. Peaking now and is among the winning hopes.
